workouts.name: Chest Press
workouts.description: Works entire chest with triceps. Variations can target specified parts of chest.
workouts.tips: Keep the weights in a diaganol grip, don't go below bending your arms 90 degrees, and keep shoulder blades pinched in the back.

workouts.name: Pec Flye
workouts.description: Works the entire chest using adduction with variations to target specific parts.
workouts.tips: Keep chin facing ceiling, arms slightly bent, and chest pushed out.

workouts.name: Dip
workouts.description: Works on triceps and lower chest using body or added weight.
workouts.tips: Keep legs behind, elbows at a 45 degree angle roughly.

workouts.name: Push Up
workouts.description: Works entire chest with triceps using body or added weight. There are a vast variety of variations for specific parts.
workouts.tips: For standard push up, keep elbows in, back flat, arms roughly shoulder width apart, go down to atleast 90 degrees with your elbows.

workouts.name: Bench Press
workouts.description: Works entire chest with triceps using a bar bell and plates. Only a few variations.
workouts.tips: keep shoulders back, plant feet firmly into ground, do not flare out elbows, the closer the grip the more triceps are used, do not go past shoulder width.

workouts.name: Leg Extention
workouts.description: Works quadriceps by extending leg using a machine, or cables.
workouts.tips: If on a machine, make sure to refer to adjustment guide to see proper adjustments. The further apart your legs the more outer quad gets worked and vice versa.

workouts.name: Leg Curl
workouts.description: Works Hamstrings by curling weight on a machie, cables, resistance bands, body weight, or dumbbells
workouts.tips: If on a machine, make sure to refer to adjustment guide to see proper adjustments. Focus on contraction in hamstrings.

workouts.name: Squat
workouts.description: Works your quadriceps and glutes by bending down at your knees and pushing your body weight, a bar bell, a risistance band, or a dumbbell back up. Several Variations.
workouts.tips: Keep feet straight, never do too much weight, keep back straight, go as deep as is confortable but atlast bend knees ast a 90 degree angle, drive through heels.

workouts.name: Leg Press
workouts.description: Works quadriceps, hips, glutes, and hamstrings by pushing yourself away using a machine
workouts.tips: Drive through heels. keep legs close to hip width apart, do not let knees come inwards, keep head back.

workouts.name: Hip Abduction
workouts.description: Works outer hips and glutes by pushing legs apart against bodyweight, risistance bands, or a machine
workouts.tips: If on a machine, make sure to refer to adjustment guide to see proper adjustments. Do not try going to wide with Abduction. Focus on contraction in hips.

workouts.name: Hip Adduction
workouts.description: Works out inner hips/groin and inner thighs by pushing legs together using most commonly6 a machine.
workouts.tips: If on a machine, make sure to refer to adjustment guide to see proper adjustments. Male gym goers do not need to go extremely heavy on this exercise due to a higher risk of hernias.

workouts.name: Calf Press
workouts.description: Works calves by pushing heels up with weight
workouts.tips: Keep toes straight, go  onto toes until a full contraction has been reached and then back down. The longer it is held the tighter the contraction for that rep will be.

workouts.name: Lat Pull
workouts.description: Works your lattimus dorsi by pulling down weight on a machine or cables.
workouts.tips: Keep grip at most shoulder width apart. Lean back only a small amount.

workouts.name: Row
workouts.description: Works a variety of back muscles depending on the variation by pulling weight towards you using dumbbells, machines, or cables.
workouts.tips: Make sure to pull in as much as comfortable for full muscle contraction.

workouts.name: Pull Up
workouts.description: Works a few areas of your back depending on grip placement by pulling your body weight, added or reduced weight up on an assisted machine, or regular pull up bar.
workouts.tips: The wider the grip the more the sides of the lats get used.

workouts.name: Straight Arm Push Down
workouts.description: Works your lattimus dorsi but pushing weight on a cable machine down with rigid arms.
workouts.tips: Stay bent over with back flat keep elbows bent but only a few degrees and rigid

workouts.name: Arm Curl
workouts.description: Works on bicep as a whole by bringing weight up laterally using dumbbells, resistance bands, cables, and more.
workouts.tips: Keep shoulders back, rotate pinky inward to activate more of the bicep.

workouts.name: Hammer Curl
workouts.description: Works on Brachus muscle in bicep, by bringing weight up with hands horizantaly.
workouts.tips: Keep shoulders back. Bring weight straight up and straight back down.

workouts.name: Tricep Extention
workouts.description: Works long head of tricep by pushing weight up using a machine, weights, risistance bands, or cables.
workouts.tips: Keep elbows foreward, do not use momentum to get weight up.

workouts.name: Tricep Press
workouts.description: Works short head of tricep by pushing weight down on a machine, with body weight, or ristance bands.
workouts.tips: If on a machine, make sure to refer to adjustment guide to see proper adjustments. Keep elbows in.

workouts.name: Jogging
workouts.description: Works on cardio. On a tread mill or out in nature, jogging is a good warm up and exercise.
workouts.tips: Stay at a steady pace and focus on breathing.
